Are all mages who can win a fight because of their CC. If you know your damage is not going to be the reason you will win a fight you can sacrifice some damage for the CC or penetration stat and still heavily contribute, if not be the reason your team won a fight.
Mages output damage typically just like ADCs and there are also clear cases of ADCs being utilized for their effects and not just the damage. Goog examples of that would be Sivir, ashe, jhin, varus. I think it is all more defined in game based on what your team needs. Your Xerath example is alright because its true he can combo and kill almost any squishy but that Q threat is a strong zoning tool in a fight. He can ult at any time to poke whether its to initiate or to clean up or even just chunk during the fight when he cant get close enough to land his normal combo. I think they avoid going overboard on mage CC/utility because a competitive team would use it paired with AP damage/ratios to an extreme solo q would probably never see but straight up damage is not something mages are or should be soley focused on.
